Fall_River.Osborn House:
The Osborn House is a historic house at 456 Rock Street in Fall River, Massachusetts, built in the Greek Revival style.


== Description and history ==
The house was designed by Rhode Island architect Russell Warren for Joseph Durfee in 1843. Four years after the house was built, Joseph Durfee died, and the house was then occupied by his daughter Elizabeth who had married William Carr in 1848.
